Junk Bond Yields Fall to Record, Bofa Merrill Index Data Show

-- B y   S a p n a   M a h e s h w a r i
-- 
2011-02-17T23:15:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/junk-bond-yields-tumble-to-record-low-7-308-bofa-merrill-s-index-shows.html
Yields on speculative-grade bonds
tumbled 4 basis points to the lowest on record today, reaching
7.308 percent, according to Bank of America Merrill
Lynch index data.  That beat the previous record of 7.312 percent set on Dec.
15, 2004, the index data show. The extra yield investors to own
high-yield, high-risk debt instead of Treasuries rose 2 basis
points to 456 basis points, or 4.56 percentage points.  High-yield, high-risk, or junk, debt is rated below Baa3 by
Moody’s Investors Service and BBB- by  Standard & Poor’s .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sapna Maheshwari in New York at 
 sapnam@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Pierre Paulden at 
